<simplesect kind="return"><para>Returns a IGeometry representing the buffered shape. </para></simplesect>
</para><para>The buffer distance is in the same units as the source shape that is being buffered. A negative distance can be specified to produce a buffer inside the original polygon. This cannot be used with polyline and must be applied on top-level geometries only. Top-Level geometries are point, multipoint, polyline and polygon. </para>        </detaileddescription>
